hematicians finally began to accept and use these perplexing numbers. Why were negative numbers considered with such suspicion? Why were they such an abstract concept? And how did they finally get accepted? With Ian Stewart , Professor of Mathematics at the University of Warwick; Colva Roney-Dougal , Lecturer in Pure Mathematics at the University of St Andrews; Raymond Flood , Lecturer in Computing Studies and Mathematics at Kellogg College, Oxford."},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p01gmz5q.jpg","duration":{"value":2700,"label":"45 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2010-05-20T11:47:55Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null}],"state":"ok","style":null,"uris":null,"total":1},{"id":"aod_tracks","type":"inline_display_module","title":"Tracklist","state":"ok","data":[]},{"controls":null,"id":"play_queue","type":"inline_display_module","title":"Coming Up Next","description":null,"image_url":null,"data":[{"id":"p003hydb","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:p003hyd9","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2006-03-09T00:00:00Z","label":"09 Mar 2006"},"titles":{"primary":"In Our Time","secondary":"Negative Numbers","tertiary":null,"e